-- Santander Hires Investec’s Pain for U.K. Auto Securitization
-- B y   A l a s t a i r   M a r s h   a n d   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 2013-08-06T12:00:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-06/santander-hires-investec-s-pain-for-u-k-auto-securitization.html
Banco Santander SA (SAN)  hired Mark Pain as
the head of securitization for its U.K. consumer unit.  The position involves funding and structuring of asset-backed securities for the bank’s auto finance business in
Redhill, U.K., according to Andy Smith, a London-based spokesman
for Spain’s biggest bank.  Pain joined from  Investec Plc (INVP) , which owns a bank and money
manager in South Africa and the U.K., where he worked from 2006.  To contact the reporters on this story:
